1. Each region has many availability zones ( usually 3, min is 3, max is 6).
Example: 
a. ap-southeast-2a
b. ap-southeast-2b
c. ap-southeast-2c
2. Each availability zone(AZ) is one or more discrete data centers with reduntant power,networking and connectivity.
3. They are seperate from each other, so that they're isolated from disasters.
4. They are connected with high bandwidth, ultra-low latency networking.